WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.980 --> 00:00:05.640
 Ingredients: Milk chocolate brick 200g Room temperature 4 eggs (about 220g) 

00:00:07.760 --> 00:00:12.560
 Eggs separate egg yolk protein 

00:00:18.920 --> 00:00:29.780
 Milk chocolate bricks chopped 

00:00:47.740 --> 00:01:11.000
 Cut out white newspapers according to the size of the baking mold 

00:01:17.920 --> 00:01:33.240
 The baking mold is coated with a layer of salt-free cream and covered with a white newspaper. 

00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:43.460
 The steel basin is filled with water and cooked to 50 degrees. 

00:01:43.460 --> 00:01:57.800
 Place the working pot containing the chocolate crumb on the top of the pot that has been cooked to 50 degrees c. Heat and melt by means of water heating. 

00:02:02.420 --> 00:02:12.620
 The protein is whipped in a high-end protein syrup (dry foaming) 

00:02:27.180 --> 00:02:34.120
 Add the egg yolk to the chocolate and mix it evenly 

00:02:41.440 --> 00:02:48.540
 1/3 serving of meringue is added to the chocolate sauce and mixed evenly 

00:02:58.720 --> 00:03:07.300
 Pour into the remaining meringue and mix evenly 

00:03:25.020 --> 00:03:31.920
 Batter poured into the baking mold and smoothed 

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:36.380
 Tap a few times on the table 

00:03:36.380 --> 00:03:44.320
 Bake in an oven that has been preheated to 170 degrees c for 28-30 minutes until the bamboo stick is inserted. 

00:03:49.060 --> 00:03:58.820
 Remove the baking mold to cool 

00:04:02.800 --> 00:04:11.600
 Completely cool off the white newspaper 

00:04:17.580 --> 00:04:25.900
 Sprinkled with powdered sugar to finish 

